stories.text:
I have a personal Dell Alienware laptop 2017 model which has started behaving very weirdly. It sometimes just crashes and then doesn't boot up for next 2-7 days. And after that it starts working again as normal and may not even crash for like 1-2 weeks or may crash the next day. Formatting hasn't helped, reinstalling windows hasn't helped, unistalling drivers hasn't helped so from a technical perspective what can be the reason?

I suspect it could be a hardware issue but am unable to come up with a conclusion.
stories.title: Ask HN: My PC sometimes boots up but sometimes doesn't, what can be the reason?

stories.text:
I'm wondering what the situation is with software development in your countries.
In Poland, the prices for software house services are growing year by year, but they are still very favorable (on average about 60 EURO). Still, I don't have any current data on how it looks in other European countries or the States.
What are the current rates for software house services in your countries?
